    "panels": [
      {
        "text": "###BEHIND THE SCENES\nIn Music & Dance with AI, students can regenerate the dancer, music, or dance if they want a new version. While this looks like “try again,” it models a bigger idea: iteration is part of how we work with AI.\n\nHere’s what’s happening in real AI systems:\n",
        "imageUrl": "",
        "key": "Generate_dancer_info-e349bed8-89d6-4efc-8a0e-29b8a1e5afb1"
      },
      {
        "text": "Probabilistic Outputs – AI models don’t produce the same answer every time. They sample from many possible options, which is why the same prompt can give varied results.",
        "imageUrl": "",
        "key": "HoAI_pilot_5_musicXI_-pl-8a94a9c7-b987-4fc6-9789-d9132de2fa9d"
      },
      {
        "text": "Temperature & Sampling – Technical settings like “temperature” control how random or conservative outputs are. A low temperature gives safer, more predictable results; a high temperature leads to more creative, but sometimes messy, results.",
        "imageUrl": "",
        "key": "HoAI_pilot_5_musicXI_-pl-7b8af0c7-0223-4c0f-9719-81f37d0affaa"
      },
      {
        "text": "Human Oversight – Because AI outputs are probabilistic, human judgment is essential. Users decide when to accept, reject, or iterate on an output.",
        "imageUrl": "",
        "key": "HoAI_pilot_5_musicXI_-pl-64f9ac9e-f602-409d-be29-7abdfb3b7bfc"
      },
      {
        "text": "Regeneration is a perfect discussion moment. Encourage students to see it not as failure, but as part of creative exploration. In practice, working with AI means experimenting, comparing versions, and making thoughtful choices — skills that align closely with growth mindset and critical thinking.",
        "imageUrl": "",
        "key": "HoAI_pilot_5_musicXI_-pl-bfa8299f-37d4-427a-9ab0-0e9b893777d4"
      }
    ],
    "name_suffix": "_-pl"
  },
